README


Installation:
------------
  Installing an archiver instance involves generating a configuration xml 
and intializing the database accordingly.

Step 1: Database intialization

  The automated script, 'ta_initdb.sh', can be used to automatically generate
the database specifics by first modifying ta_dbcredentials.conf with the 
following options:

TNMS_DBUSER=
TNMS_DBPASS=
TNMS_DBHOST=

 The script will generate the necessary SQL, create the database, and exec
 the SQL via the main tnms config script 'tnms_dbinit.sh'. 
 
 This script will assume all SQL is exec'd by the root sql account. If your 
 database 'root' user is not named 'root' or you wish to use a different 
 account, then you should run the 'tnms_dbinit.sh' script by hand. 
 
  1. First run 'ta_createdbsql.sh' with the unique instance name, 
     which will be the name of the database, and a filename; the 
     script will generate and write the sql schema to this file.

  2. Run the 'tnms_dbinit.sh' script using the -D and -f options 
     providing the database name and sql file generated in step 1, 
     respectively, and providing the db account details with proper 
     permissions for creating the database.
     (see 'tnms_dbinit.sh --help' for more details)

